1} the distribution reduces to the Cauchy distribution. For @math{a = 2}
it is a Gaussian distribution with @c{$\sigma = \sqrt{2} \mu$}
@math{\sigma = \sqrt@{2@} \mu}. For @math{a < 1} the tails of the
distribution become extremely wide.

The algorithm only works for @c{$0 < a \le 2$}
@math{0 < a <= 2}.
@end deftypefn

